<body>
        
    
<div>
    <Markdown>
        ### Demos
        
        #### /pokemon-dots:
        Using `[...page.astro]` and `[slug].astro`

        * ✅ [/pokemon-dots](/pokemon-dots)
        * ✅ [/pokemon-dots/bulbasaur](/pokemon-dots/bulbasaur)
        * ❌ [/pokemon-dots/page/2](/pokemon-dots/2)
        * ❌ [/pokemon-dots/3](/pokemon-dots/3)

        #### /pokemon-page:
        Using `[page.astro]` and `[slug].astro`
        * ✅ [/pokemon-page/bulbasaur](/pokemon-page/bulbasaur)
        * ❌ [/pokemon-page](/pokemon-page)
        * ❌ [/pokemon-page/2](/pokemon-page/2)
        * ❌ [/pokemon-page/3](/pokemon-page/3)

         #### /pokemon-pagination-only:
        With only `[...page.astro]` present the pagination works fine:
        * ✅ [/pokemon-pagination-only](/pokemon-pagination-only)
        * ✅ [/pokemon-pagination-only/2](/pokemon-pagination-only/2)
        * ✅ [/pokemon-pagination-only/3](/pokemon-pagination-only/3)

         #### /pokemon-workaround:
        It is possible to sort of work-around this by adding a `page` directory, but this is a bit inconvenient.
        * ✅ [/pokemon-workaround](/pokemon-workaround)
        * ✅ [/pokemon-workaround/page/2](/pokemon-workaround/page/2)
        * ✅ [/pokemon-workaround/page/3](/pokemon-workaround/page/3)
        * ✅ [/pokemon-dots/bulbasaur](/pokemon-dots/bulbasaur)
    </Markdown>
</div>
